# SSL Certificate Directory

This directory will contain SSL certificates for HTTPS.

## For Production:

Place your SSL certificate files here:
- `cert.pem` - SSL certificate
- `key.pem` - Private key

## Using Let's Encrypt:

```bash
certbot certonly --standalone -d yourdomain.com

# Copy certificates
cp /etc/letsencrypt/live/yourdomain.com/fullchain.pem /root/coms/nginx/ssl/cert.pem
cp /etc/letsencrypt/live/yourdomain.com/privkey.pem /root/coms/nginx/ssl/key.pem
```

## Self-Signed Certificate (Testing):

```bash
openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey rsa:2048 \
  -keyout key.pem -out cert.pem \
  -subj "/C=KE/ST=Nairobi/L=Nairobi/O=COMS/CN=156.232.88.156"
```

**Note:** Certificate files (*.pem, *.key) are excluded from git for security.
